This article summarizes a joint press conference held by President Giammattei of Guatemala and Vice President Harris of the United States. They discussed their shared goals of addressing the root causes of migration and promoting economic development in Guatemala. They emphasized the importance of providing hope and opportunities for Guatemalans to stay in their home country, rather than having to migrate. They also discussed the need to combat corruption and strengthen the judiciary system in Guatemala. Additionally, they announced plans for collaboration on issues such as security, human trafficking, and economic empowerment for women. The press conference touched on the United States' commitment to provide vaccines to Guatemala and the importance of international cooperation in addressing global challenges. Finally, Vice President Harris addressed criticism regarding her visit to the border and emphasized the significance of her role as the first female vice president representing the United States abroad.